    • Uses of Input in Services

      Methods in Services with parameters of type Input 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Response Service.fillService(Input data)
      The interface method for a user to access a service
      Response RegisterService.fillService(Input data)
      Creates a user using the provided information.
      Response PersonService.fillService(Input data)
      This method checks if a person id number was supplied.
      Response LoginService.fillService(Input data)
      Logs a user into the server; checks if the userName is in the database, and if so checks to see if the supplied password matches generates an authToken and returns it.
      Response LoadService.fillService(Input data)
      Calls the clear service method, then takes the list of data from the input and creates users and persons for each user populates the database with newly created users, then it adds the events to the database
      Response FillService.fillService(Input data)
      Populates the server's database with generated data for the specified user name.
      Response EventService.fillService(Input data)
      If an event id is supplied, this returns information about the event, otherwise it returns all events that belong to the user with the authToken
      Response ClearService.fillService(Input data)
      Deletes all the tables from the database
